Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. Hearing on February 28, 2022 at 01:00 pm.

01:18 PM  District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Ronald Alvarez in court, in custody, with attorney Raymond Henry LaBarge.  Attorney LaBarge states he is here for the limited purpose of addressing bond but states they can address setting the preliminary hearing as well.  State indicates they are prepared to proceed on the Motion.  Attorney LaBarge presents arguments in support of the motion to modify bail.  State has no objection to reducing bail to $10,000.00 so long as WCS monitoring remains as a condition of bond.  The Court places findings on the record and denies the Motion to Modify Bail.  Bail remains as fixed.  Attorney LaBarge states he does not have an agreement with the defendant to represent beyond this matter.  The defendant states he is not willing to waive the time but wishes to have counsel.  The Court provides the defendant with the Petition for Court Appointed Counsel and will set this matter back on Monday during lockups.  The Court will further set this matter for a bail hearing before the Trial Court next week.  Court tolled time limits for preliminary hearing.  Hearing scheduled for February 28, 2022 at 01:00 pm.
